georouting.node
Class ImaginaryNode

java.lang.Object
  georouting.Node
      georouting.node.ImaginaryNode

public class ImaginaryNode
extends Node

An imaginary is more of a point than a node, but can be used in conjunction with "real" nodes in order to compute distance / angles. An Imaginary Node may not be placed into a graph. As a side effect, Imaginary Nodes may not be used when constructing Edges (Unless I introduce an ImaginaryEdge :D)
